# ESG Funds in Europe: Code and Data Replication

This repository contains the complete Python code and supporting materials used to generate the results in the research paper:

**"ESG Funds in Europe: Performance, Structural Patterns, and Predictability in High-Dimensional Financial Data"**  
*Marco Pellegrino, 2025*

## ğŸ“„ Paper Abstract

The study investigates whether European ESG funds systematically differ from non-ESG funds in terms of risk-adjusted performance, latent structural patterns, and predictability from financial fundamentals. Leveraging a large-scale, cross-sectional dataset of over 67,000 mutual funds and ETFs (as of December 2023), the analysis combines econometric models with machine learning techniquesâ€”including PCA, t-SNE, K-Means clustering, and logistic regression. The findings show that ESG funds exhibit modestly higher Sharpe ratios, partial clustering under non-linear projections, and moderate predictability (~64%) of ESG status based on financial features.

